tip.text: Their food is definitely good (not budget friendly) but the ambiance n service justifies the price. Their lunch set deal of $22 is definitely worth the money.
Excellent service and the low carb super bun option is actually tasty! Highly recommended.
Really good food, excellent views. House wine for $55 for a bottle!! That is the reshmi kebab -  must have!
Very pricey. Ended up spending  $60 for ramen, gyoza n a drink  (×2). Not Impressed!

venue.name: Menya Musashi Kodou 麺屋武蔵

tip.text: OMG... sheer foodgasm. Forget the staff who cares... the burgersss are awesome. I'm in love with their chilli con carne burger whilst wishing I could stuff the triple bacon burger down too!!
You are paying for the ambience and quality of food & service. Order their starters, I had the buffalo cheese with fresh pesto, olive tapenade! Don't forget the vanilla panacotta -yum!

formattedAddress: Terminal 2 Arrival Hall, Changi Airport (Airport Blvd.)

tip.text: Order the stir fried pork with chilli. The grilled whole chicken has nothin thai about it and tom yum is not too spicy n more of tomato flavour. Great option if you want low carb food otherwise skip.
Really good classes, came for a morrocan session. Chef Charlotte was great and super fun to learn with.
The selection of the wine we had. Amazing staff! Great tapas cheap and big portions. Perfect ambience, my new fave in CPH.
Their tokyo stew  is my fave. Smoked salmon sandwich for those extra hungry days. Both amongst the lowest in calories but oh so yummy!
Please do not order seafood here. My salmon for $16.90 was so stale, couldn't eat more than a bite! Same with the seafood baked rice
Do NOT order pineapple chicken fried rice. There is no chicken whatsoever. For $11.90 I regretted every bite of the few I had. When asked they said it was finely minced. Spot the chicken!
OMG.. strawberry cheesecake waffles are to die for! Worth every penny & calories!!
The boneless chicken is really good. Had the platter with Calamari rings, boneless with very hot spicy sauce (recommended ) and wings (with classic sauce).
Everything! Amazing service, great food, perfect ambience, great value for money. Huge portions and so tasty!
Their Ayam Taliwang is really good. Not too spicy, very local & yummy! Happy with most of their dishes: massamun, green curry, pizza, snapper in garlic butter. Great ambience in the evenings!
